  "id": "019d2ddf-1f74-7142-91d7-54865cd8bace",
  "content": "# Tiered Knowledge Design Progress (March 2026)\n\n## 5 Memory Types (Decided)\n- **Structural**: Code signatures, API shapes from ingestion. No decay — refreshed on re-ingestion.\n- **Decisional**: Design decisions, architectural choices, \"why\" rationale. Very slow decay, needs confidence score.\n- **Episodic**: Session discoveries, agent activity, debugging. Fast decay unless reinforced by access.\n- **Analytical**: Synthesized findings, health checks, cross-repo patterns. Medium decay, superseded by newer analysis.\n- **Procedural**: Instructions, workflows, how-to patterns. Slowest decay, reinforced by every access.\n\n## 4-Tier Lifecycle (Decided)\n- **Hot**: HNSW indexed, full retrieval participation\n- **Warm**: HNSW indexed, retrieval deprioritized\n- **Cold**: NOT in HNSW, embedding preserved, searchable via brute-force fallback. Automatically promoted on access (cold → warm).\n- **Forgotten**: Compacted into summary entry, original archived. Original embedding discarded, summary gets new embedding. Only irreversible step.\n\n## Key Design Decisions\n1. Tiers are about **storage lifecycle**, not retrieval ranking (two separate systems)\n2. Cold is reversible — \"hibernation, not death.\" Entries auto-promote on access.\n3. Memory type determines decay profile (how fast entries move through tiers)\n4. Retrieval priority is downstream of tier classification, not the same system\n5. Working memory curation (what enters agent context) is a retrieval-time concern, not a tier concern\n6. Confidence score needed on Decisional/Analytical entries\n7. Session/agent affinity boosts are retrieval-layer concerns, not tier concerns\n\n## Schema Additions Planned\n- `memory_type: MemoryType` enum (Structural, Decisional, Episodic, Analytical, Procedural)\n- `confidence: Option<f32>` (0.0-1.0)\n- `last_accessed: Option<DateTime<Utc>>`\n- `access_count: u32`\n- Auto-classification from existing content_role for backward compatibility\n\n## Open Questions\n- What other domains/dimensions need exploration beyond tier classification?\n- Forgetting policy configuration (per-scope? per-type? global?)\n- Compaction strategy (how to merge entries into summaries)\n- Cold storage search: brute-force vs secondary HNSW index\n- Budget constraints: hard limits or soft pressure?",
